MultiPixel Monetization Compliance Guide
Relimintor (Raptor4 / MultiPixel)

1. PURPOSE
This guide explains how monetization works for Mods and Servers under the
MultiPixel License 2.2.

2. WHAT COUNTS AS REVENUE
Revenue includes:
• donations
• tips
• subscriptions
• lootbox purchases
• in-game currency purchases
• cosmetic/VIP role purchases
• advertisements
• sponsorships
• crypto payments
• barter or in-kind payments
• any transfer of value

3. APPROVAL REQUIREMENTS
a. Mods require explicit written approval to monetize.
b. Servers require explicit written approval to monetize.

4. REVENUE SHARE
• Mods: MultiPixel receives 15% of gross revenue.
• Servers: MultiPixel receives 30% of gross revenue.

5. REPORTING REQUIREMENTS
Creators must:
• maintain accurate revenue records
• provide reports upon request
• use approved payment platforms
• comply with audits

6. ALLOWED MONETIZATION
• lootboxes
• in-game currency
• cosmetic/VIP roles

7. PROHIBITED MONETIZATION
• gambling
• crypto/NFTs
• selling progression
• selling admin/mod roles
• pay-to-win (unless approved)
• unapproved monetization of any kind

8. CONSEQUENCES
Violations may result in:
• fines
• tariffs
• legal action
• server shutdown
• mod removal
• permanent bans
